Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Mince the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced) and @parsley{1%bunch}(minced). Thinly slice the @portobello mushrooms{4%oz}(thinly sliced).

Grate half the remaining onion into a #medium bowl{}. Then, mix in the @ground beef{2%oz}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @nutmeg{1/4%tsp}, @allspice{1/4%tsp}, half the garlic, and half the parsley. Season with a large pinch salt and @pepper{pinch}. Roll into meatballs about 1-inch in a diameter.

Place meatballs on one side of a #baking sheet{}. On the other side, toss mushrooms with @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper. Place in the oven for ~{15-20%minutes}, until meatballs are cooked through and mushrooms are browned.

Meanwhile, add the @egg noodles{} to the boiling water and cook for ~{8-10%minutes}, until al dente.

While the noodles cook, heat @butter{1/2%tbsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the sliced onion and cook, tossing, for about ~{5%minutes}, until softened. Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Add @veggie stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup}. Simmer until reduced by half. Stir in the @sour cream{4%tbsp} and cook for ~{2%minutes} more, until sauce has thickened slightly.

Once the noodles are ready, drain, reserving @pasta water{1/4%cup}. Add egg noodles, meatballs, and roasted mushrooms to the pan. Toss until combined. Add a splash of pasta water if the sauce becomes too thick. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Serve with a sprinkle of remaining parsley and enjoy!